Nice park to do a picinic, to play with the kids, to take a walk. It has a playground and a sandbox.
Beautiful park!

Nice hidden gem of a green space in 16th Paris. Has two playgrounds for different aged kids, beautiful walking paths, a water fountain. Not much noisy either. A must go if you live around and have a small kid. I regret not having discovered this park earlier.
Pretty cool park.
Wallace fountain ‚úÖ
Very nice good job

Park accessible free of charge, located between avenue de la Porte d'Auteuil and Square du Tchad, and giving access to the Jardin des Serres d'Auteuil from its northern end. A corner of greenery where you can stroll peacefully, even next to the daughter of spectators of the Roland-Garros tournament along the avenue de la Porte d'Auteuil üòÆüíö  It also has free public toilets, between the access near Porte d'Auteuil and the north end, too bad they are dirty! This reduces the comfort of walking in this park, which is pleasant to do on foot, with strollers and wheelchairs, especially since the offices are too small to enter with your wheelchair!

Great! Still as well maintained, looking forward to sunny days. On the edge of the Serres d'Auteuil, the Jardin des Po√®tes commemorates more or less famous Poets. Plaques and busts among century-old trees. Easy access from Porte d'Auteuil.
Very beautiful square at Porte d'Auteuil, it overlooks the greenhouses which can be visited. A haven of peace and freshness, with shaded and sunny spaces.

Very nice place to breathe a little nature. You can run and do gymnastic exercises in the open air and in peace... There are two play areas for children... one area with facilities for toddlers and others for older children.  The other area is a sandbox where the cleanliness of the sand leaves something to be desired even if the place is well maintained. Gardeners at work... a free book exchange showcase to circulate those we no longer want is a real plus.

A magnificent square where it is good to rest and regenerate. We still hear a lot of cars (at the edge of the ring roads) but we quickly forget for those who know how to let themselves be absorbed by the green and wooded environment.
A well-maintained park but too close to the ring road‚Ä¶ it however has more of its place in this ocean of noise and olfactory pollution

Very well maintained, this square is as charming as it is surprising. Good size, this green space adjacent to Rolland Garros is full of majestic trees, incredible greenhouses each with their own specificity, a space for children‚Ä¶. In short, enough to spend some wonderful hours there.
Very beautiful park, very clean and very well maintained. A real joy for both children and adults.

Well, for Pushkin 5, of course On a slightly more serious note, it‚Äôs a decent, nice little garden, a little noisy in some places, but it doesn‚Äôt bother you much when walking. In May there is a smell of flowers, there are centuries-old trees, and what else is needed for a good garden. Also, this garden is slightly separated from the neighboring one, so it is possible to visit two gardens at the entrance to one.
Cute corner of greenery (1954) near the Auteuil greenhouses. Walkways honor ancient poets, with remarkable trees Very pleasant square where children can play To have !

Square extremely noisy because of the hellish traffic on the expressways which surround it. This is a shame. The park is decorated with beautiful and large trees. Statues and busts of poets line the paths, paths which can be walked around in 15 minutes (provided you can tolerate the noise).
Superb and very pleasant for children!!!!
Rather pretty, communicates with the Auteuil greenhouse garden

A very nice and clean park. You can come for a mini picnic))) There is a place for games for children. There is a pump station with drinking water and a toilet in the park. Very good location. A supermarket and a racetrack are located next to the park. bus station N¬∞ 32, 52, 123, 241, PC. Metro N¬∞ 10 direction Boulogne-Billancourt. I recommend it for relaxing at the weekend.
A quiet place, with play areas for children (and adults!)

Relaxing place for everyone, young and old. Beautiful shaded trees, plants, English garden to spend the hot summer. Exotic plants can be found in the Serres Auteuil... As for the rest of the new things, it's up to you to discover them.
very large park
This is a beautiful place that makes you forget a somewhat ugly modern neighborhood. What a shame that in the poets' square the plaques are mostly illegible. Otherwise the walk is worth a look.
A place where poetry is honored through poets represented by magnificent statues and extracts from their works engraved and on stones and plaques in the middle of a wooded area.

The garden or square of poets is located on the edge of the 16th arrondissement, extending the garden of the Auteuil greenhouses. It was created by Pascal Bonetti, honorary president of the Society of French Poets. There are busts of poets as well as verses from famous French poets.
Small, well-designed park with a children's play area but very noisy because of the very close ring road (even on Sundays)
Very pleasant square for walking of course only downside a little noisy and the toilets very dirty and broken the door no longer closes and there was water hello waste üò†üò° ‚Ä¶
Very beautiful little garden. The quotes from the poets are an attraction in themselves. Very pleasant to wander around there
For summer it's great, we're not in direct sunlight. The negative point is the toilets, really not practical for children.
Very green, shady, very pleasant to visit during high heat, not too many people
I played there as a child. It's been over 50 years Nostalgia
Very nice to let the children play there before or after visiting the Auteuil greenhouses!
Nice, not many people but noisy because next to the ring road and Porte d'Auteuil...
Very nice ‚ò∫Ô∏è but there are so many people
Square between the Porte d'Auteuil and the Auteuil greenhouse garden where you can read some poems on plaques dedicated to many French and foreign poets.
Obsolete cars blast from all sides of the A13 Porte d'Auteuil ring road, your ears are ringing when you get home
